        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-16T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-16T11:00:00-05:00" n="667" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d667">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 PW/8–1645: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-16T17:00:00+01:00">August 16, 1945—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 16—3:41 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>8299. Refer despatch 145 dated June 23.<note n="5" xml:id="d667fn1">Not
                        printed.</note> From Hodgson. War Crimes Commission adopted Commission
                    document C. 122 at meeting of Aug 15. Chinese representative informed Commission
                    that Chungking Subcommission approved the document. [Hodgson.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
